Nvidia has announced it is ending GeForce support for 32-bit operating systems. “Game Ready Driver upgrades, including performance enhancements, new features, and bug fixes, will be available only on 64-bit operating systems,” said Nvidia. The change is effective from April 2018, it added. “Critical security updates will be provided for 32-bit operating systems through January 2019.” The operating systems affected include: Software upgrades with new features, security updates, and bug fixes for the GeForce Experience will also only be available on Windows 64-bit operating systems.